snippet.textDisplay:
Liverpool have become a better team without Coutinho. Plus, Liverpool have Gini, Oxlade Chamberlain, Kieta on that left of midfield spot. Also have Mane, Minamino as a left sided forward. Liverpool got the absolute maximum price for him when they sold him to Barca for £142m (crazy money) and reinvested it in Van Dijk and Allison. Liverpool are also less predictable when Coutinho was in the team. They have the front 3, but also Robertson and TA bombing down the wings. Lallana will probably leave in the summer but would rather give Curtis Jones the chance to jump up to challenge for a midfield spot. On balance don’t buy back Coutinho.


What Liverpool really need is cover at left back in case Robertson goes down injured. Milner can cover there, but never a fan of right footed left backs.

snippet.textDisplay: I can't believe some Liverpool fans are bitter about Coutinho leaving them.  Believe it or not, Klopp had moved on from him. He tried to turn him into a proper midfielder, but Coutinho simply doesn't have the energy level to play in a Klopp midfield.  Klopp gave up on the idea of him ever playing there--Brazil tried him there in the WC, and Tite admitted that it left Brazil open.  He most likely would have been rotated with the players in the front three, which I don't think would have made Liverpool better.
snippet.textOriginal: I can't believe some Liverpool fans are bitter about Coutinho leaving them.  Believe it or not, Klopp had moved on from him. He tried to turn him into a proper midfielder, but Coutinho simply doesn't have the energy level to play in a Klopp midfield.
